narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned how to communicate with other clinicians about my clients' progress, as well as obstacles and difficulties with clients. I learned how to ask for help and advice regarding these clinical matters.
I learned about case conceptualizations from a variety of theoretical frameworks. I benefitted from consultation and engaging in group discussions.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Strengths: relative lack of structure gave student clinicians freedom to discuss topics most relevant to their work with clients, generally supportive atmosphere

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes. Group supervision is a time to engage in discussion about your own clients as well as those of your peers. It's a great environment for learning, planning, and reflecting.
